    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> Febr. 12<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1779</dateline><salute>Dear
                    Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>Please to accept the promised <rs type="art" ref="ar0007">print</rs>.<note type="editorial">The print has not been identified.</note> I am sorry I
                    cannot offer you <rs type="art" ref="ar0008">that of myself</rs>: many reasons inducing me to make that venal. It may be had at
                        <persName ref="pe0141">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Majors</persName>
                    <placeName ref="pl0781">St Martin's lane</placeName>. I hope next winter
                    to pass some time in <placeName ref="pl0699">town</placeName>; &amp; to enjoy a little of y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Company. Pray excuse the second tax I put on you by requesting the
                    inclosed may be directed to <persName ref="pe0323">P. Panton esq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></persName>
                    N<hi rend="superscript">o</hi> 12 <placeName ref="pl1991">Serles street</placeName>
                    <placeName ref="pl0782">Lincolns inn</placeName> <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName>. I am with much esteem</p>
                <closer><salute>Dear Sir <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>obliged &amp; most
                        obedient <lb/><sic>humbl</sic> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Thomas
                    Pennant</persName></signed></closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
